        "none": [
          "National Aeronautics and Space Administration",
          "Environmental Protection Agency",
          "Office of Manned Space Flight"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Historical Context"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "The Skylab Program was proposed as the United States' first space station, intended to expand human understanding of space and Earth through scientific research. While there was some public interest and concern regarding the environmental implications of launching rockets, the overall impact was deemed negligible by NASA. Ultimately, Skylab was successfully launched in 1973 and operated until 1974, providing valuable data and paving the way for future space exploration efforts."
        ]
      }
    },
